why should – is calling on the phone now

00:14:39.649 --> 00:14:44.339
or transcribing voice calls are, like -- and
people end up hopping into different technologies

00:14:44.339 --> 00:14:49.089
because they have these different idiosyncratic
properties but really that notion of permanence

00:14:49.089 --> 00:14:51.209
being per medium is kind of orthogonal, right?

00:14:51.209 --> 00:14:59.370
It's more how does the technology work and
what policies are around it?

00:14:59.370 --> 00:15:20.750
And that seems like somewhere where we think
about a lot in the context of Gmail where

00:15:20.750 --> 00:15:36.400
it's sort of sometimes synchronous, sometimes
asynchronous, sometimes ephemeral, sometimes

00:15:36.400 --> 00:15:38.420
permanent.

00:15:38.420 --> 00:15:45.320
