Next question.

00:46:57.060 --> 00:46:58.109
&gt;&gt;Audience: Yeah.

00:46:58.109 --> 00:47:02.300
I feel, like -- first of all, thanks, guys.

00:47:02.300 --> 00:47:10.010
And it's terrific work and it's great to see
all of the new improvements as well in the

00:47:10.010 --> 00:47:11.010
progress.

00:47:11.010 --> 00:47:20.020
But I feel like there's an elephant in the
room and it's about to hit 500 million users.

00:47:20.020 --> 00:47:27.589
Where are we around Facebook and Facebook
Connect and Open Graph?

00:47:27.589 --> 00:47:28.589
Right?

00:47:28.589 --> 00:47:35.180
Would Google -- would you guys ever think
about putting a Facebook Connect button on

00:47:35.180 --> 00:47:36.180
your sites?

00:47:36.180 --> 00:47:37.180
If not, why not?

00:47:37.180 --> 00:47:42.770
How -- how could all of the work that you
guys are doing also inter-operate well with

00:47:42.770 --> 00:47:44.900
this enormous monster that's down the road?

00:47:44.900 --> 00:47:45.900
[pause]

00:47:45.900 --> 00:47:47.710
&gt;&gt;Chris: Who wants to take it?

00:47:47.710 --> 00:47:54.380
&gt;&gt;Joseph: Yeah. Yeah, no. It's -- it's obviously
a great question and it's -- it's one where

00:47:54.380 --> 00:48:00.420
I think there is a lot of good news.

00:48:00.420 --> 00:48:09.310
I mean, Facebook's gotten very involved in
a lot of work on open standards and there's

00:48:09.310 --> 00:48:13.790
just this internet identity workshop this
week which has been kind of the grass roots

00:48:13.790 --> 00:48:20.550
place where a lot of us get together and work
on these things and Facebook's one of the

00:48:20.550 --> 00:48:25.210
most active and forward-thinking participants
and they -- they -- in fact they shipped OAuth

00:48:25.210 --> 00:48:31.461
2.0 as their authentication mechanism for
all their new Graph API stuff even as it's

00:48:31.461 --> 00:48:36.619
still in draft they were one of the first
to ship Activity Streams or in their feeds.

00:48:36.619 --> 00:48:47.880
So anyway, there's a lot of different issues
to work out in a lot of different dimensions

00:48:47.880 --> 00:48:55.380
but I think it's just great to see that the
platform keeps opening up, it keeps getting

00:48:55.380 --> 00:49:01.290
more liberal, and it keeps operating for more
of these interoperability scenarios to take

00:49:01.290 --> 00:49:02.290
place.

00:49:02.290 --> 00:49:03.730
I think it's a very positive direction.

00:49:03.730 --> 00:49:04.730
[pause]

00:49:04.730 --> 00:49:05.730
&gt;&gt;David: Thanks.

00:49:05.730 --> 00:49:07.980
I'd also add that there are Google apps that
 - today, like YouTube, that are well integrated

00:49:07.980 --> 00:49:11.930
with Facebook and do auto sharing to Facebook
so, where there are some product by product

00:49:11.930 --> 00:49:15.810
choices about wherever it makes the most sense
for users.

00:49:15.810 --> 00:49:22.010
I -- I'd also say that, the -- the -- the
elephant in the room, the story of the eight

00:49:22.010 --> 00:49:23.930
blind men and the elephant.

00:49:23.930 --> 00:49:30.160
Facebook in the area of social, there's many
different aspects and that's why there are

00:49:30.160 --> 00:49:34.160
many different answers and many different
parts of it.

00:49:34.160 --> 00:49:35.650
And you asked about the Open Graph API but
you actually probably meant the Graph API

00:49:35.650 --> 00:49:44.910
which is much less open than the Open Graph
API and it covers a different part of the

00:49:44.910 --> 00:49:49.170
space and they're both interesting things
but there's a large -- a large set of details

00:49:49.170 --> 00:49:50.630
to talk about.

00:49:50.630 --> 00:49:51.630
[pause]

00:49:51.630 --> 00:49:56.110
&gt;&gt;DeWitt: One other thing I'd add to that.

00:49:56.110 --> 00:49:57.110
David's absolutely right.

00:49:57.110 --> 00:49:59.420
There is actually no Open Graph API.

00:49:59.420 --> 00:50:04.550
There is a Open Graph Protocol and a Graph
API.

00:50:04.550 --> 00:50:11.800
But speaking of open things, I mean, it's
definitely in Google's best interest to work

00:50:11.800 --> 00:50:17.210
with Facebook, work with twitter, work with
all of these, these elephants to figure out

00:50:17.210 --> 00:50:20.100
what the common protocols could be.

00:50:20.100 --> 00:50:22.240
What other things could we build?

00:50:22.240 --> 00:50:24.390
Could we build an open connect?

00:50:24.390 --> 00:50:25.770
Could we build an OAuth?

00:50:25.770 --> 00:50:26.770
An OpenID?

00:50:26.770 --> 00:50:31.359
And use all of us working together to help
make the web itself more social.

00:50:31.359 --> 00:50:35.950
I don't think ultimately Google does very
well if we get everybody implementing only

00:50:35.950 --> 00:50:38.250
a very strictly Google-branded version of
this stuff.

00:50:38.250 --> 00:50:45.030
We do much better when the entire web is implementing
the same connect protocol because that's in

00:50:45.030 --> 00:50:50.440
our interest and, and I honestly believe it's
in, twitter or Facebook's best interest to

00:50:50.440 --> 00:50:52.230
do this as well.

00:50:52.230 --> 00:50:58.430
We'll go out of our way to work with 'em on
these things.

00:50:58.430 --> 00:50:59.430
[pause]

00:50:59.430 --> 00:51:06.240
&gt;&gt;Chris: Could you expand that a little bit
why it's in our best interest?

00:51:06.240 --> 00:51:10.900
&gt;&gt;David: What's good for the web is good for
Google.

00:51:10.900 --> 00:51:11.900
&gt;&gt;DeWitt: Yeah.

00:51:11.900 --> 00:51:12.900
It is so simple.

00:51:12.900 --> 00:51:16.080
I mean, our business was born on the web.

00:51:16.080 --> 00:51:19.210
It will be on the web forever.

00:51:19.210 --> 00:51:21.530
The web is much, much bigger than Google.

00:51:21.530 --> 00:51:24.740
The web is much bigger than Facebook.

00:51:24.740 --> 00:51:28.020
And to the extent that we can continue to
grow the web, Google as a business does well.

00:51:28.020 --> 00:51:30.610
Plus, I think a lot of us here just personally
believe that.

00:51:30.610 --> 00:51:33.390
It's not just the business.

00:51:33.390 --> 00:51:37.430
Like, we wake up every morning going, hey,
I wanna fight for this.

00:51:37.430 --> 00:51:38.690
Like, this is exciting.

00:51:38.690 --> 00:51:43.210
&gt;&gt;Joseph: Yeah. I was gonna say, it motivates
